          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a Hindu philosophical treatise written from the perspective of the Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta school of philosophy and addresses issues like the nature of the Self (ātman) as the ultimate principal in the universe with a particular focus on the concept of imperceptible (aparokṣa) inference (anubhūti).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Aparokṣānubhava</title>
              <title type="vernacular">अपरोक्षानुभव</title>
